<br>
 Why had she come back to the amazon lands?<br>
<br>
 For a few moments Dawn remained silent, rolling the hilt of a dagger between her two hands as she pondered the answers that were more appropriate to give to Shey, and then the answers that her athelfi was more likely to go hunting for-knowing they existed. Then Dawn looked up at Shey, taking a deep breath she prepared her answer and then spoke.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I came back because of my athelfi. I'm not much of an amazon sister anymore, nor do I request that I become like I was. I'm quite happy with the reputation that the Amazon Nation has for me, and carries with it in its stories. But I came back for my athelfi. I came back to check on my daughter whose taken over Orio-Pata, to check on my students who've created their own tribe with a power triad of Queen's.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn gave a bit of a shrug. So it wasn't the answer she knew Shey would be looking for.. but it was an answer none the less.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I just came back. Not quite sure why. Just back.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn glanced to Anya and then Shey, laughing lightly.<br>
<br>
 &quot;And you two are not old.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sheyala>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 473<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/03 5:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gemstone.net/etimes/et5/images/faerie-queen.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mind and body</span><hr size=1> Shey smirked as the old assassin weighed her mind with her answer. She guessed, no expected it. And she knew it wasn't the whole truth. She hadn't lied, but she hadn't said everything. Shey left it at that, because neither did she. She hadn't expanded on where she had been or why, she hadn't touched on why she had come back to this place that held so many fresh wounds. Sartha was one of the largest, but that was somewhere neither of them dared to go. Then, she began to laugh.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And you two are not old.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Massaging her wrists she smirked with the irony of it. &quot;My mind says that still, but my body disagrees with me Dawn. You see, we have lose our immortality friend, and time is catching up with us since we have cheated it so badly. Joints ache in rain, cold in the morning encourages one not to get up. Some days Anya can barely keep up with me and the horse. Not that I was ever able to keep up with a horse mind you...&quot; She smiled, knowledge in her century old eyes that Dawn shared too.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not ancient perhaps, not old, but perhaps older.&quot; She raked a hand through her hair, and if one looked close enough silver threatened the roots in her part. However, she was ever still the warrior, now commanding the Black Mare. &quot;Something no normal person would complain of I suppose, but when one has lived so long and never aged it is a strange thing. So, what made you come and visit...&quot; She paused a moment abnd continued choosing her words to be humerous as she waivered her voice like an old woman. &quot;This old maid and her geriatric wolf?&quot; In jest Anya rolled over barring her stomach acting as if she couldn't get up. Shey chuckled and smiled in her bemused way. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
&quot;Aut Pax Aut Bellum&quot;<br>
(Either Peace Or War)<br>
May the gods smile uponthe peace and magesty of the phoenix.. The ways of Sheyala Rose..<br>
